  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "0i21PNnzwzfj7kS/NV4Ze5ac6kw=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Every document model has a **document type** - a namespaced identifier that uniquely identifies it across the ecosystem. Format: `namespace/model-name` (lowercase with hyphens).\n\nExamples:\n- `powerhouse/todo-list`\n- `my-org/todo`\n\nThis identifier is used to:\n- Link editors to their document models (`documentTypes: [\"powerhouse/todo-list\"]` in manifest)\n- Create new document instances of a specific type\n- Query documents by type across drives\n- Register document models in Reactors\n\nThe document model name in Vetra Studio uses PascalCase (e.g., `TodoList`) while the document type uses lowercase-hyphenated format. Capitalization matters because it influences code generation (type names, function names, etc.).",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
    }
  },
